<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Nev. Killers Sentenced  </HEADLINE>
By LISA SNEDEKER
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Two lovers were sentenced to life in prison
Friday for killing wealthy gambling figure Ted Binion and stealing
at least $5 million worth of his silver fortune.
</P>
<P>
   Rick Tabish will be eligible for parole in 25 years and Sandra
Murphy will be eligible in 24 years under the sentence from
District Judge Joseph Bonaventure.
</P>
<P>
   The pair was convicted of first-degree murder for killing Binion
on Sept. 17, 1998. Binion's family owns the Horseshoe Club in Las
Vegas.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors say Murphy and Tabish forced Binion, 55, to ingest a
cocktail of heroin and the prescription drug Xanax, then suffocated
him. The defense claims Binion, who was involved with Murphy, died
of an accidental overdose or suicide.
</P>
<P>
   The judge called Tabish, a Missoula, Mont., contractor, a con
man and berated Murphy, a former exotic dancer.
</P>
<P>
   ''Your bland indifference and your attitude shows little
respect,'' Bonaventure said. ''You chose to betray and kill your
lover and now you must live with the consequences. Maybe you will
finally awaken from this 'Alice In Wonderland' dream state.''
</P>
<P>
   Bonaventure called Murphy's involvement in the crime
''horrific.''
</P>
<P>
   ''You presented yourself as a caring, loving girlfriend only to
lure him (Binion) into a trap that ultimately cost him his life.''
</P>
<P>
   Defense attorneys have promised to appeal. Tabish and Murphy
each reiterated their innocence to the judge.
</P>
<P>
   ''It wasn't an evil plot,'' Tabish said. ''It didn't happen.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I shouldn't even be here,'' added Murphy.
</P>
<P>
   David Mattsen, who once tried to collect a $100,000 reward for
information in the Binion case, and Michael Milot face a Nov. 13
trial in the case.
</P>
<P>
   Two days after Binion's death, Mattsen, Milot and Tabish were
arrested while trying to dig up Binion's silver from an underground
vault in Pahrump, 55 miles west of Las Vegas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
