<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia 3, Peru 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Looking to reclaim its world dominance
in women's volleyball, Russia swept past Peru in the first round of
the Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
   Elena Godina had 14 kills and the Russians took less than an
hour to record the 25-17, 25-13, 25-20 victory Saturday (Friday
night EDT).
</P>
<P>
   Russia, ranked No. 1 in the world, is regarded as having the
best chance to unseat Cuba, which won gold in 1992 and '96.
</P>
<P>
   The Russians have four gold medals and three silvers in the
eight Olympics in which they have participated. Their only blemish
was a fourth-place showing in Atlanta four years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Eleventh-ranked Peru, which had to beat Argentina in five sets
to qualify for the Olympics out of the South American zone,
committed 23 errors to 18 for the Russians.
</P>
</TEXT>
