<HEADLINE> Henderson in 2nd Place on Runs List  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BALTIMORE (AP) -- Rickey Henderson scored two runs for the
Seattle Mariners on Friday night to move past Babe Ruth and Hank
Aaron into second place on the career list.
</P>
<P>
   Henderson has scored 2,175 runs, one more than Ruth and Aaron
and trailing only career leader Ty Cobb (2,245).
</P>
<P>
   Batting leadoff against the Baltimore Orioles, Henderson tied
Ruth and Aaron in the first inning when he tripled and scored on a
