<HEADLINE> Leftists Attack German Neo-Nazis  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEUMUENSTER, Germany (AP) -- Leftist demonstrators threw a hail
of bottles and stones Saturday at around 500 neo-Nazis protesting
the closure of their local hangout.
</P>
<P>
   Police took more than 100 people into custody. No injuries were
reported.
</P>
<P>
   Leftists split from a simultaneous counter-demonstration in
Neumuenster, just north of Hamburg, that drew some 800 people.
Among them was Schleswig-Holstein state governor Heide Simonis, who
appealed for vigilance against neo-Nazis and violence against
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
   About 1,300 police kept the leftist and neo-Nazi marchers apart,
but the leftists threw stones, bottles and other objects.
</P>
<P>
   Police said 101 people were taken into temporary custody and 17
charged with resisting police orders.
</P>
<P>
   City officials revoked the club's license and ordered it closed
Sept. 5 after determining it was being advertised on the Internet
as a hangout for neo-Nazis.
</P>
