<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-16 17:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Giuliani breaks loose  </HEADLINE>
By VERENA DOBNIK
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) - A day after undergoing major treatment for
prostate cancer, Mayor Rudolph Giuliani was billed as ''amazing''
on Saturday for marching two dozen blocks in a Manhattan parade.
</P>
<P>
   Then he sprang loose, enjoying a private walk home on a sunny
Manhattan afternoon, including a drugstore stop.
</P>
<P>
   The mayor appeared to be operating at full force again, stepping
off at noon in the German-American Steuben Parade up Fifth Avenue.
Wearing a cap inscribed ''Mount Sinai'' - the hospital where he
underwent the procedure Friday - Giuliani said the doctors there
''did it in such a skillful way that I'm able to march.''
</P>
<P>
   At the start of the parade route at 63rd Street, Rep. Rick Lazio
and Yankees owner George Steinbrenner greeted Giuliani with hugs.
''You're amazing!'' Lazio whispered in his ear.
</P>
<P>
   The mayor proceeded up Fifth with Lazio and Steinbrenner,
followed by Judith Nathan, a woman Giuliani has called his ''very
good friend.''
</P>
<P>
   At the end of the parade route at Park Avenue and 86th Street,
the mayor held a news conference - as he had done on Friday, barely
five hours after radioactive seeds were implanted in his cancerous
prostate. His doctors said the treatment went ''perfectly'' and
called the mayor' prognosis ''excellent.''
</P>
<P>
   After Saturday's parade, Giuliani dove into the crowd on the
sidewalk, shaking hands and chatting before ducking into the
drugstore.
</P>
<P>
   Then, accompanied by only a handful of people, including Nathan,
he walked toward Gracie Mansion, greeting surprised passersby and
spreading his jovial mood in all directions - including diners at a
corner restaurant, one of whom yelled out, ''How are you feeling?''
</P>
<P>
   At the sight of the pedestrian mayor, a car heading toward a
crosswalk to avoid traffic suddenly veered back on track.
</P>
<P>
   And when a little boy on his bicycle recognized Giuliani, he
turned to his mother and said, ''Look, it's the mayor!''
</P>
<P>
   She responded: ''Is it? I didn't recognize him.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
