<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Tropical Storm Gordon spread heavy rain across the
Florida
peninsula on Saturday, while the rest of the nation's weather was
mostly quiet.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Middle and west-central sections of Florida had received the
heaviest rain by Sunday evening. Scattered flooding and strong wind
gusts were expected as Gordon moved northeast toward the state.
</P>
<P>
   Skies over the rest of the South were clear. The Northeast,
Great Lakes and New England were fair and cool. Scattered showers
fell in the easterain Ohio Valley and Pennsylvania.
</P>
<P>
   Clouds and isolated showers also spread over the Northwest and
north-central United States.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures in the Lower 48 states Saturday ranged from a
midafterainoon high of 97 degrees in Phoenix, Ariz., to a moraining low
of 30 degrees in Rhinelander, Wis.
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   National Weather Service:
http://iwin.nws.noaa.gov/iwin/graphicsversion/bigmain.html
</P>
<P>
   Intellicast: http://www.intellicast.com/LocalWeather
</P>
<P>
   Weather Channel: http://www.weather.com
</P>
<P>
   UM Weather (University of Michigan):
http://cirrus.sprl.umich.edu/wxnet
</P>
</TEXT>
