Colo. Fire Causes Home Evacuations
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   BOULDER, Colo. (AP) -- Flames leapt from tree to tree and shot high into the
air today as a wildfire raged through almost 500 acres west of the city,
prompting authorities to call for the evacuation of 200 mountain homes. A plume
of smoke thousands of feet high was visible from Fort Collins, nearly 50 miles
away.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Canadian Wins Men's Triathlon Gold
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Canadian Simon Whitfield climbed back after a crash
in the bike race, then sprinted past Germany's Stephan Vuckovic in the final 200
meters of the running segment to win the Olympic men's triathlon. Whitfield,
wearing a new bathing suit that arrived only hours earlier from Canada, thrust
his arms in the air as he crossed the finish line in 1 hour, 48 minutes, 24
seconds.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Tao Luna of China Wins Air Pistol
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Tao Luna of China started strong and carried it
through to win the Olympic women's 10-meter air pistol Sunday (Saturday night
EDT). Tao tied the Olympic mark with a qualifying score of 390 and went on to
win with 488.2 points. Jasna Sekavic of Yugoslavia won the silver with 486.5 and
Annemarie Forder of Australia scored 484 to take the bronze.
AP NewsBrief by GRETCHEN SCHWARTZ 
</P>
