<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Arrested for 3 Ind. Slayings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAKEVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Police arrested four people Saturday in
connection with the execution-style killings of three construction
workers found dead inside a barn where they were installing a loft.
</P>
<P>
   The bodies of Wayne A. Shumaker, 59; Corby Myers, 30; and Lynn
Ganger, 54, were found Thursday afternoon by a co-worker.
</P>
<P>
   Each victim had been shot in the head, and all were found with
their hands tied behind their backs, said Mike Swanson, commander
of the St. Joseph County Special Crimes Unit.
</P>
<P>
   Swanson said the three workers may have stumbled upon a burglary
attempt. ''It appears they were caught by surprise,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Lee Washington Jr., 20, and Phillip A. Stroud, 21, both
of South Bend, were arrested on preliminary charges of murder in
the killings, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Also arrested were Curtiss F. Smith, 24, of South Bend, and
Charity Lynn Payne, 18, of North Liberty. Smith was arrested on a
preliminarily charge of assisting a criminal, and Payne was
arrested on a preliminary charge of burglary, investigators said.
</P>
<P>
   The barn where the bodies were found is in a rural area midway
between Lakeville and Lapaz in St. Joseph County, about 25 miles
south of South Bend.
</P>
<P>
   Swanson said Saturday that more arrests were possible.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the victims' relatives struggled to cope with the
killings.
</P>
<P>
   ''It doesn't seem real,'' said Vonna Miller, a sister of Wayne
Shumaker. ''There' no reason for it.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-09-16-00 2233 </TRAILER>
