<HEADLINE> Fire forces evacuation at Catskill resort  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ELLENVILLE, N.Y. (AP) - A smoky fire at a storied Catskill
Mountain resort Saturday forced the evacuation of more than 300
guests.
</P>
<P>
   Only minor injuries were reported after the 12:50 p.m. fire at
The Nevele Grand Hotel in Ellenville, in Ulster County about 75
miles northwest of New York City. A handful of guests and two
firefighters were treated at the scene for smoke inhalation, said
Ellenville Fire Chief Tom Coniker.
</P>
<P>
   The fire started in a maintenance closet next to a ballroom at
the hotel. Coniker said fire damaged only the closet but smoke
spread throughout the eight-story building where 850 people were
staying.
</P>
<P>
   Of the guests, less than half had to be evacuated, Coniker said.
The hotel was back in full swing later Saturday after firefighters
used 17 high powered fans to clear the building of smoke.
</P>
