<HEADLINE> Lumberyard fire burns through the night  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LEE CENTER, N.Y. (AP) - A fire at a family-owned lumberyard
burned throughout Friday night and much of the day Saturday, doing
about $2 million worth of damage.
</P>
<P>
   The fire broke out shortly before 11 p.m. Friday at Bowers &AMP;
Sons Hardwood Lumber, an architectural supply specialist that
produces things like stairs, custom flooring, doors and moldings.
</P>
<P>
   Saturday afternoon, piles of melted machinery were all that
remained at the nearly 20,000-square-foot storage and manufacturing
building. Firefighters, who pumped hundreds of thousands of gallons
of water on the blaze Friday night, continued to put out hot spots
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   It will be at least Monday before investigators can get on site
to search for a cause.
</P>
<P>
   The family said it plans to rebuild the business started in
1979. They have insurance.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's obviously a major setback,'' Jonas Bowers told the
Observer-Dispatch of Utica. ''We're going to press forward and do
what we have to do.''
</P>
