<HEADLINE> Devils 5, Penguins 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WILKES-BARRE, Pa. (AP) -- Sylvain Cloutier and Jay Pandolfo
scored third-period, power-play goals to lead New Jersey to a 5-4
exhibition victory over the Pittsburgh Penguins on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   With the score tied at 3, Cloutier beat Penguins goalie
Sebastien Caron at 7:41 of the third. Just over five minutes later,
Pandolfo fanned on a shot, but the puck still slid through Caron's
pads.
</P>
<P>
   The defending Stanley Cup champion Devils, playing their
preseason opener, jumped out to a 3-0 lead in the opening 9:25 of
the first period. Ed Ward scored 34 seconds into the game, Colin
White tallied at 2:12 and Steve Kelly netted a short-handed goal at
9:25.
</P>
<P>
   Goals by Alexei Kovalev, Martin Straka and Robert Lang rallied
the Penguins to a 3-3 tie.
</P>
<P>
   Aleksey Morozov's goal with 32 seconds left in the third put the
Penguins within a goal. But with 4.4 seconds left, Devils goalie
Frederic Henry gloved a deflection of a Toby Petersen shot.
</P>
